verbose_text: In mice, the Sry gene locates to the minimum sex determining region of the murine Y chromosome XREF_BIBR, is expressed in the male genital ridge at the time of sex determination XREF_BIBR and has been proven to be a sex determining gene based on gain-of-function experiments, i.e., the overexpression of Sry in XX mice achieved with transgenic mouse technology reveals a male phenotype XREF_BIBR.
